Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.98,0:00:06.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The star of a show is usually charming.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.65,0:00:07.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,However, the same could be said for the culprit or victim...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.24,0:00:09.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Today is the conclusion to the case!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.82,0:00:11.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The angel will finally come down.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.24,0:00:13.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We must find the real treasure!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.15,0:00:14.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Seeing through to the one and only truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.55,0:00:16.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I look like a child, but have the intellect of an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.22,0:00:18.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,450)}My name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.26,0:01:45.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A girl asked the Detective Boys for help.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.76,0:01:48.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Her name was Matsunaka Yuriko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}, from the class next door.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.59,0:01:57.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The case was to solve a riddle left by her great-grandfather, Gozoushi Isegawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.09,0:02:02.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Afterwards, we followed the instructions of a mysterious man named "Tokei".
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.01,0:02:06.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then went to Angel's Mansion to hear the puzzle and search for clues.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.08,0:02:15.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now it's time...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.65,0:02:19.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...for me to announce the riddle.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.12,0:02:21.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"When the bull's horn disappears,"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.93,0:02:23.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"and its tail becomes its head,"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.25,0:02:27.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"the angel comes down and starts playing the horn."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.29,0:02:29.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"That melody is my treasure."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.92,0:02:35.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.01,0:02:38.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So, that's why...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.01,0:02:38.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, hurry and-!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.76,0:02:39.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, hurry and-!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.59,0:02:44.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,3000)}Yuriko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.31,0:02:47.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The Mysterious Angel's Mansion,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.11,0:02:48.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Part 2!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.19,0:02:56.61,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Angel of the South: Dungeon
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.15,0:03:02.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, guys... Are you alright?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.73,0:03:05.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.86,0:03:07.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Same here, even though it was a long fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.79,0:03:10.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Genta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, Genta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.64,0:03:13.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Help! Genta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} is...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.22,0:03:15.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Genta! Genta!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.17,0:03:20.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Another bowl of eel rice, please...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.46,0:03:23.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He hasn't slept since yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.46,0:03:28.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Genta, the time limit is only 9 hours now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.68,0:03:32.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Where am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.73,0:03:36.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just like Tokei{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} said,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.33,0:03:41.99,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The Angel's Mansion is like a huge labyrinth.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.42,0:03:43.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Labyrinth..
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.74,0:03:44.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Labyrinth!?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.91,0:03:48.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What do we do? There's nothing we can do but wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.15,0:03:51.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.80,0:03:55.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, there's no way out?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.22,0:04:02.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mitsuhiko, it's all your fault!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.15,0:04:03.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why me?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.93,0:04:07.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right! You were trying to show off to Yuriko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.63,0:04:09.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and yet you got nothing in spite of your eagerness.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.39,0:04:11.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If that's true, it's also your fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.52,0:04:15.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You said you wanted to beat Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} and went off on your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.30,0:04:17.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Haibara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Ayumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} did as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.35,0:04:19.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was just...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.32,0:04:21.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.86,0:04:24.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,you ran into the Angel's tower, acting all self-righteous.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.67,0:04:26.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that why this happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.26,0:04:29.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, why didn't you guys wait outside and watch?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.58,0:04:31.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say, Conan?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.26,0:04:34.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying it's our fault Yuriko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} got captured?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.08,0:04:35.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You want to fight?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.96,0:04:37.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Bring it on!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.39,0:04:50.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Cut it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.85,0:04:54.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop fighting! Aren't we friends?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.71,0:04:57.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But he said it was my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.34,0:04:59.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If the Detective Boys are fighting,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.67,0:05:02.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's going to rescue Yuriko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.83,0:05:04.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She's always lonely.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.57,0:05:06.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She's alone even now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.34,0:05:11.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.46,0:05:12.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.24,0:05:15.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.34,0:05:18.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan apologized?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.02,0:05:19.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.59,0:05:22.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything will be alright, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.19,0:05:24.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,With the united power of the Detective Boys,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.60,0:05:26.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,even two labyrinths mean nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.68,0:05:28.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.09,0:05:32.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It must be really tiring trying to cheer up the kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.51,0:05:33.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.35,0:05:35.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Mitsuhiko...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.63,0:05:36.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.64,0:05:40.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That skeleton you found in the Eastern Mansion...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.36,0:05:41.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Which way was its head facing?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.32,0:05:45.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The direction? I think it was...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.20,0:05:46.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is south,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.86,0:05:49.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and from here to the east Mansion...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.26,0:05:51.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was facing that way!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.81,0:05:54.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was pointing towards the fireplace and facing down.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.66,0:05:56.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,According to what Tokei{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} said,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.86,0:06:00.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,it was a thief who got lost and died in the labyrinth.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.16,0:06:02.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We know its head is facing down,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.38,0:06:04.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and that the head is pointing towards the exit.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.84,0:06:09.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mitsuhiko also confirmed that the bones' location is connected to the fireplace.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.76,0:06:14.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That means this labyrinth must be\Nconnected to the Eastern Mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.14,0:06:16.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow! I knew Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} could figure it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.97,0:06:21.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But, the question is how we can get from here to there,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.02,0:06:22.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,before we turn into skeletons as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.95,0:06:25.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The Minotauros's Labyrinth.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.12,0:06:29.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Remember? It was here, in front of the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.37,0:06:32.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The half-man, half-bull creature.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.61,0:06:34.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,According to Greek mythology,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.28,0:06:38.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Minotauros was born to a Cretan King, who had offended God.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.25,0:06:40.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So he inherited the blood of a bull.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.92,0:06:44.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The Minotauros grew up to be a frightful, brutal beast,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.61,0:06:49.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so the King of Crete sent his own son into the "Labyrinth of No Return."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.42,0:06:52.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Will something like that be here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.21,0:06:53.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.68,0:06:59.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The important thing is that...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.10,0:07:05.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,the King would annually send seven Athenian children into the labyrinth as tributes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.12,0:07:08.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When the hero Theseus heard of this,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.78,0:07:12.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,he went to challenge the labyrinth, and defeated the Minotauros.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.50,0:07:15.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He returned from that so-called "Labyrinth of No Return",
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.12,0:07:18.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,using just a ball of yarn.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.75,0:07:19.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yarn?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.96,0:07:21.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How could yarn help?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.00,0:07:25.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah... He tied one end of the yarn to the labyrinth's entrance,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.97,0:07:27.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and let it unwind itself as he walked.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.67,0:07:31.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,To return from the labyrinth, he just followed the yarn back to the entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.26,0:07:32.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.91,0:07:34.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.22,0:07:35.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll do it too...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.18,0:07:36.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, me too!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.32,0:07:39.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have to, being a girl and all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.66,0:07:40.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.76,0:08:11.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like we've gone in a circle.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.24,0:08:16.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So at that corner, we should have turned right instead of left.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.62,0:08:20.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay, Mitsuhiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.70,0:08:22.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.23,0:08:24.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't catch a cold at such an important time...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.89,0:08:39.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Do we have enough?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.11,0:08:41.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But at least we're closer to the exit now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.20,0:08:44.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to help too!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.00,0:09:01.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.69,0:09:03.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.26,0:09:05.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's our job to find the way out,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.85,0:09:08.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and it's your job to solve the riddle.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.67,0:09:09.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Genta?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.61,0:09:15.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. Everyone should do what they are best at.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.03,0:09:18.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mitsuhiko, you guys...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.78,0:09:21.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.93,0:09:24.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, is the time limit up?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.20,0:09:26.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I solved the second part of the riddle.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.89,0:09:27.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.74,0:09:29.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Found it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.35,0:09:31.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Over there, it's him!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.50,0:09:34.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That means we're close to the exit!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.41,0:09:45.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We're saved.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.87,0:09:47.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That was so scary.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.61,0:09:52.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuriko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.55,0:09:56.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay, Yuriko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.26,0:09:56.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you hurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.90,0:09:58.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.09,0:10:00.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You wanted to kidnap Yuriko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} from the start.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.92,0:10:01.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.97,0:10:05.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I just wanted to save Yuriko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} from the trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.66,0:10:12.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was just scared, since he grabbed my wrist so suddenly.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.16,0:10:14.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry that I worried you,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.20,0:10:17.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and also that I caused you so much trouble...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.49,0:10:20.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,N-no. It was fun, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.80,0:10:25.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. It was like an adventure.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.23,0:10:26.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wasn't it, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.13,0:10:28.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.73,0:10:37.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Edogawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, you said you had solved the second part of riddle, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.50,0:10:38.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.20,0:10:40.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But, we only have 3 hours left.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.49,0:10:42.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's impossible to get the treasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.30,0:10:43.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.66,0:10:46.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The part with "And its tail becomes its head," indicates the direction "ne," which is north.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.54,0:10:49.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"Ne" also means midnight.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.54,0:10:55.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In order words, the Northern Mansion will only open at midnight.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.84,0:10:58.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Our time limit will be up at 9:00 PM tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.37,0:10:59.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.99,0:11:02.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Tokei{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.33,0:11:05.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You had already solved the first part of the riddle, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.89,0:11:10.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why you didn't care who found the dark crystal,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.27,0:11:12.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so you only saved Yuriko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.51,0:11:15.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, you purposely let us fall into the labyrinth to waste our time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.32,0:11:18.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There are only 3 hours left.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.99,0:11:21.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I wish for your success from the bottom of my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.85,0:11:49.31,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Only one hour left.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.77,0:11:52.63,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The way to open that Angel's door,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.63,0:11:54.36,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}is it really gone?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.41,0:11:57.62,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Everybody is trying their best.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.62,0:12:00.26,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Think back carefully, think back carefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.42,0:12:04.32,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}"When the bull's horn disappears, and its tail becomes its head,"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.83,0:12:07.30,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}"the angel comes down and starts playing the horn."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.30,0:12:09.73,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}"That melody is my treasure."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.32,0:12:16.46,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The angel's really scary...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.31,0:12:20.80,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It couldn't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.80,0:12:22.72,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}But if that's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.37,0:12:32.77,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I see. That's why it's like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.77,0:12:34.26,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Ladder.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.26,0:12:35.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Get a ladder!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.11,0:12:41.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Uncle, where is the ladder?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.23,0:12:44.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The direction of "ne" is at the Angel of the North, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.65,0:12:46.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the Angel of the East, the east.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.93,0:12:48.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,East?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.62,0:13:11.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Be careful, Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.55,0:13:11.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Good luck!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.04,0:13:32.95,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Just like I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.65,0:13:37.17,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Now, let's see where it is...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.86,0:13:48.06,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}This is the horn that we've been waiting for.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.05,0:13:51.47,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The moment the light strikes the Angel of the North.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.78,0:13:56.81,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}"The angel comes down and starts playing the horn" made from that dark crystal.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.11,0:13:59.31,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}"That melody is..."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.51,0:14:16.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Look over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.53,0:14:18.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The angel came down to the forest!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.50,0:14:20.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.04,0:14:24.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the shadow, the shadow of the angel playing its horn.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.22,0:14:26.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"That melody is {\i1}my treasure{\i0}."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.71,0:14:29.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's on the hill by the fire house.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.02,0:14:30.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a shadow of the horn.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.68,0:14:32.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the melody of the angel.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.76,0:14:34.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.47,0:14:36.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And we still have 30 minutes left, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.43,0:14:37.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.95,0:14:41.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Tokei{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.53,0:14:53.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That treasure belongs to Yuriko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.06,0:14:55.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're an adult. Stealing other people's treasure is cruel.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.75,0:14:56.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Tokei{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.35,0:14:59.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not it. You misunderstood me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.07,0:14:59.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuriko...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.19,0:15:04.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't get in my way, there's no time left.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.66,0:15:23.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did it have to be another labyrinth?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.52,0:15:39.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's so shiny!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.35,0:15:43.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the treasure left by Isegawa Gozoushi,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.67,0:15:46.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuriko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}'s great-grandfather?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.16,0:15:50.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That is...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.56,0:15:55.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Game over, Tokei{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.40,0:15:57.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell us the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.81,0:16:01.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You were after the treasure from the very beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.28,0:16:02.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,As his secretary,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.81,0:16:06.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,you were the first to hear the riddle, and you had solved it entirely.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.06,0:16:07.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Entirely?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.72,0:16:12.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There was, however, a timing error in your deduction.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.03,0:16:14.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The evidence of which, is the announcement of the riddle at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.28,0:16:17.78,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Unfortunately, it's not time yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.09,0:16:20.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If the riddle is announced at night,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.28,0:16:24.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,you would have to wait until the next afternoon to open the tower of the Angel of the North.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.50,0:16:25.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After solving the second part of the riddle,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.79,0:16:29.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,even if the challenger noticed the Angel of the North's tower,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.29,0:16:32.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,they would have to wait until midnight to open the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.22,0:16:36.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Therefore, no matter who the challengers were, it would be an impossible task to accomplish in just 24 hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.34,0:16:38.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like that, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.10,0:16:40.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.07,0:16:42.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If he was after the treasure from the very beginning,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.51,0:16:44.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,after Isegawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} passed away,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.30,0:16:45.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,he could have tested his deductions,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.98,0:16:47.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and found their flaws.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.76,0:16:52.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, he couldn't test his deductions yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.09,0:16:54.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If he did, then it would've been a crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.21,0:16:58.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He wanted the money legally.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.49,0:17:00.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Legally?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.51,0:17:02.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, Tokei{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.33,0:17:05.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,is the eighteenth heir.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.73,0:17:11.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why he erased all the clues left by the former challengers,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.50,0:17:16.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and at the same time scouted us out, while secretly waiting for his turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.44,0:17:17.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.55,0:17:22.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was my lord, Isegawa Gozoushi, who instructed me to announce the riddle at 9:00 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.00,0:17:24.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You think we'd believe you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.20,0:17:26.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I believe him,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.98,0:17:27.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,because of the knife.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.98,0:17:32.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was meant to warn us about the power grid.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.42,0:17:34.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The escaping footsteps were that of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.65,0:17:37.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and there's only one adult here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.95,0:17:40.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't to scout or to confuse us,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.20,0:17:43.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I believe that it was all to protect Yuriko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and the rest of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.80,0:17:48.54,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}There are traps that are even more horrific than the security devices my lord installed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.98,0:17:53.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think Tokei{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is a bad man either.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.05,0:17:54.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuriko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.37,0:17:58.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Because at that moment...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.32,0:18:18.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's obvious.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.54,0:18:21.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The ones abandoned by their family are hated by them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.43,0:18:23.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}, that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.34,0:18:26.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Although he is Isegawa Gozoushi's secretary,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.84,0:18:29.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,he would not have been allowed to solve the family riddle,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.80,0:18:32.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,unless he was somehow related to Isegawa Gozoushi.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.65,0:18:35.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's related to my great-grandfather?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.71,0:18:39.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But Isegawa Gozoushi deprived him of his last name,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.02,0:18:40.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and forced him to carry out his will.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.93,0:18:44.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So, until the riddle was solved, he had to remain here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.27,0:18:45.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thus, he's a hated man.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.03,0:18:49.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So, it has to be him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.53,0:18:51.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You, could you be...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.19,0:18:53.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's enough questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.86,0:18:57.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What Tokei{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} wants is not the gold...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.11,0:18:57.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...but that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.04,0:19:03.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuriko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.38,0:19:06.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, that's his granddaughter,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.99,0:19:09.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Tokei{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.75,0:19:13.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then that means Tokei{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is Yuriko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.23,0:19:14.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's her father.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.84,0:19:18.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's also Isegawa Gozoushi's most hated relative.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.98,0:19:21.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The one who satisfies all these requirements,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.24,0:19:24.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,is the one who ran away with Yuriko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}'s mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.68,0:19:28.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Isegawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s most treasured person before he passed away...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.65,0:19:31.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,was his cute granddaughter, Yuriko's mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.87,0:19:33.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He said she looked like his former wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.44,0:19:35.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So, no matter the cost,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.04,0:19:40.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,he would try to get his granddaughter, who ran away with me, back.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.74,0:19:46.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He was affilated with the Yakuza.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.33,0:19:49.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Once he was angered, his actions became unpredictable.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.58,0:19:55.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In order to protect her and the newborn Yuriko,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.96,0:20:00.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I vanished from their sight and met with Isegawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.90,0:20:03.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In turn, I promised to work for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.32,0:20:06.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,To soothe his anger, I worked for him with all my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.35,0:20:10.94,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}My lord, it is windy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.38,0:20:15.35,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}But, I like it like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.15,0:20:21.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So, I understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.49,0:20:24.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In his heart, he deeply loved his family,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.95,0:20:26.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,he just never showed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.83,0:20:29.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He seemed ill-tempered,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.92,0:20:35.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but he was just a kind old man longing to be with his family.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.67,0:20:39.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Last year, Isegawa Gozoushi suddenly said he wanted to see...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.64,0:20:43.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...his granddaughter, Yuriko's mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.12,0:20:45.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So I went to find her.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.72,0:20:48.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's when I discovered that she had passed away.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.64,0:20:53.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Isegawa was disappointed and became sick.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.13,0:20:57.17,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Announce the riddle at 9:00 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.17,0:21:00.46,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Once the riddle is solved, you will be free.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.46,0:21:02.86,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Forgive me, Matsunaka{\rHonorifics - Flashback\be10}-kun{\r\be10}.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.74,0:21:09.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My real name is Matsunaka Yoshito.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.64,0:21:11.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Yuriko's dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.90,0:21:16.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Your mother also tried to solve that riddle when she was your age.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.99,0:21:18.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.21,0:21:19.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.67,0:21:24.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But, your great-grandfather said that only his great-granddaughter would be able to solve the riddle,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.42,0:21:26.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and that leaves only you, Yuriko.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.66,0:21:28.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I think that's what he honestly thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.08,0:21:33.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.81,0:21:36.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuriko, I'm so sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.35,0:21:38.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Forgive me, Yuriko.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.32,0:23:19.28,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The Angel's Mansion and the fake skeleton ended up becoming a theme park based upon bulls and labyrinths.
